<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Blin_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Phonology">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Phonology">Phonology</span></h2>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Blin_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Consonants">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Consonants">Consonants</span></h3>
<p>Note: <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/tʃ/</span> is found in loans and the status of <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/ʔ/</span> as a <a href="/wiki/Phoneme" title="Phoneme">phoneme</a> is uncertain.</p>
<p>/r/ is typically realised as a <a href="/wiki/Flap_consonant" title="Flap consonant">tap</a> when it is medial and a <a href="/wiki/Trill_consonant" title="Trill consonant">trill</a> when it is in final position.</p>
